remarks.text: Suspension of Work due to Tropical Storm "Enteng".

BLR transmitted the 3rd revised copies to Areas 1 to 4 LREs for review.
LREs reviewed the 3rd revised copy.
Areas 1, 3, and 4 were able to review the revised copy of TX and TM as soon as we forwarded it to them, however for Area 2, there are some evaluators assigned to some quarters who we're unable to get the copies of TX and TM on time due to their schedule.
remarks.status:
LREs reviewed the 3rd revised copy.
Areas 1, 3, and 4 were able to review the revised copy of TX and TM as soon as we forwarded it to them, however for Area 2, there are some evaluators assigned to some quarters who we're unable to get the copies of TX and TM on time due to their schedule.

remarks.text: The evaluators are sending back the copies of their TX and TM per area of evaluation.

Transmitted the 3rd revised copies to the publisher.
Vibal and its development team revised the TX and TM based on the result of the LREs findings.

BLR-QAD received the 4th revised copy.

LREs gave immediate comments and recommendations for the Book cover and forwarded the suggestions to the publisher.
BLR-QAD transmitted the 4th revised copy to Areas 2 to 4 LREs who aren't available to receive the books last September 24, 2024.

Forwarded the comments and recommendations of the LREs about the cover art of the TX and TM.
BLR got the revised book cover for the TX and TM that the LREs and forwarded it to the LREs
The same day, the LREs approved the revised book cover.

Forwarded the TX and TM copy for sign off.
The LREs started signing off the pages.

The LREs completed signing off the TX and TM. Forwarded the following pages to the publisher that are not signed off due to some errors found by the evaluators while signing off the pages: TX: 15, 16, 17, 30, 33, 37, 42, 45, 50, 67, 80, 179, and 183; TM: 11, 20, 22, 25, 145.

The revised pages was sent to the BLR and forwarded imidiately to the evaluators.
The evaluators approved the remaining pages
Transmitted the letter requesting for the RTP copies of the TX and TM.
Received the RTP copies and transmitted it to BLRPD for Conformance checking.
The books are expected to be returned on November 28
